script = ExtResource("3_us72x")
category = 5
text = "Born slightly before his mortal enemy Marutol, Lithduga grew up and lived in a village slightly north-west of the centre of Bauland. Lithduga faced a similar fate to most Ancient Baulandian men, being a soldier that protected the people. Ultimately being promoted to Vice General of the forces, Lithduga served under General Marutol for half of his regular army life whilst being in charge of over 40 towns and villages. Though when Marutol's warmongering began, things took a wild toll on Lithduga.

Swiftly after finding about what Marutol was doing, he started ignoring orders and remained stationary in a single village ready for battle with Marutol, but he never came. Turns out, Marutol was too busy conquering and destroying every other village near Lithduga's all the way up until the coast. Lithduga was struck with guilt for not trying to help the innocents sooner, by trying to be honourful he lost the oppurtunity to stop his General and got fumed by a fit of rage. Lithduga took his remaining forces and made his life mission to start this destined battle with Marutol even if it meant chasing him around the whole of Elvus.

After also figuring out sea travel, Lithduga arrived to Terranica late but stronger. Loss on soldiers was not nearly as damaging on Lithduga's regiment as he was much more caring and cautious. But knowing that Marutol took over a whole continent already and estimating how far he has come since then, the Vice General knew that he had to power himself and his army up. Over 50 years, whilst Marutol was building an army of undead to conquer the continent, Lithduga was training to become strong enough to take him down. During those 50 years, Lithduga's men found a blade so unique no one has seen one like it before. It was called the Kurakaraka and it is one of the earliest Artifacts known to be found. The Kurakaraka was a large blade imbued with a powerful soul on its metal. If one is to control the Kurakaraka, they could summon all of the elements from the blade as it was swung. After a year of learning swordplay, Lithduga deemed his strength worthy to challenge Marutol which he knew was also building up forces, and so he went to battle.

After arriving it was tough for Lithduga and his men, the overwelming forces of skeletons and soldiers was too much to handle. After not even a few hours, half of Lithduga's men lost their lives and even turned against their old comrades. But Lithduga's focus was purely on killing the man who's ruined Bauland's civilization. By the time Lithduga reached Marutol, he was unaware that those two were the only live people left in the compound, the battle was the last of it all. The Kurakaraka was immensly strong, alongside the shock factor it handed Lithduga, but it was not enough. Over those 50 years, Marutol was experimenting with ways Life magic can be used to increase ones battle prowess and it was too much for Lithduga. Despite killing Marutol and forcing him to flee into the World's Core, Lithduga died from his injuries. This revenge was not enough for Lithduga to get freed from his guilt, his willpower was too weak to fight off Marutols necromancy and ironically joined back with his mortal enemy to fight for his cause again."
id = 13
name = "Lithduga"
